===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms}}

Usually related to {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s/m/g-rus||bone}}, whence {{cog|bo|རུས}}, {{cog|ii|ꃷꅍ|'''ꃷ'''ꅍ}}, {{cog|ksw|တၢ်ဃံ|တၢ်'''ဃံ'''}}, but there is no trace of a medial {{m|und|*r}} in Chinese ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Luce (1981)}} compares {{cog|my|ခုတ်|t=to chop, hew}}, which appears phonetically much closer, as well as semantically reasonable, if animal bones were interpreted as "hewed pieces".

